column3: An entity is any organisation with which a person makes or intends to make a contractual agreement, and which is the second party in a contract
The human individual or person whose personal data or privacy is involved, and which is the first party in a contract
The Service Provider involved as the Second Party in the contractual interaction
A party other than the Person and Entity as first and second parties respectively in the contractual interaction
A legal authority that is empowered to investigate and determine compliance
An agent that represents a party and can act on behalf of it - such as for signing contracts or negotiating terms
column9: Agents can be human or non-human i.e. machine agents

column3: The party that is responsible for a specific activity

An Agent is any software or a combination of software and hardware that works exclusively for its party, and which may be provided by a third party but must be controlled and be responsible to the party it represents
An Agent that represents the Person
An Agent that repersents the Entity
